{
  "texts": [
    "For both categories, we split the works into NER and NED.",
    "Research works on English Named entity recognitionThe most used approach for NER is \"coarse-grained\", which considers entities belonging to a small number of major classes (from one to ten).",
    "Most of the research studies focusing on a single class are dedicated to bio-medical NER: they extract the names of diseases, viruses, patients, etc.",
    "The work focusing on three classes aims to extract person, location and organisation names [83].",
    "The works focusing on four classes tend to focus on identifying person, location, organisation, and miscellaneous names [44,162,187]."
  ]
}